p: Among them, I, I k and I d represent measurement, kinetics and limit diffusion current density, n is the number of electrons transferred by oxygen reduction, F is the Faraday constant, A (cm 2) is the geometric area of the electrode, k is the rate constant of the reaction, and C 0 is the oxygen constant in a saturated 0.1 M KOH solution, D is the oxygen diffusion coefficient, ν is the solvent dynamic viscosity, and ω is the speed in rad s −1.
